  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "What is الاسم الممدود?",
      "titleArabic": "تعريف الاسم الممدود",
      "content": [
        "الاسم الممدود is a noun ending in alif followed by hamza (اء), like السَّمَاء (sky), الدُّعَاء (supplication), and الصَّحْرَاء (desert).",
        "Unlike المقصور and المنقوص, the ممدود takes visible case endings on the hamza."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Ends in اء (alif + hamza)",
        "Takes visible case endings: السَّمَاءُ، السَّمَاءَ، السَّمَاءِ",
        "Common examples: السَّمَاء، البِنَاء، الدُّعَاء، الصَّحْرَاء",
        "Fully declines like regular nouns"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "السَّمَاءُ زَرْقَاءُ", "english": "The sky is blue" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ السَّمَاءَ", "english": "I saw the sky" },
        { "arabic": "نَظَرْتُ إِلَى السَّمَاءِ", "english": "I looked at the sky" },
        { "arabic": "الدُّعَاءُ مُسْتَجَابٌ", "english": "The supplication is answered" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Types of Hamza in الممدود",
      "titleArabic": "أنواع الهمزة في الممدود",
      "content": [
        "The hamza in الممدود can be original (أصلية), for feminization (للتأنيث), or transformed (منقلبة). This affects how the noun forms its dual and feminine.",
        "Original hamza stays in all forms. Feminization hamza changes to و in dual (صَحْرَاوَانِ)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Original hamza (أصلية): stays as hamza - قُرَّاء → قُرَّاءَانِ",
        "Feminization hamza (للتأنيث): changes to و - صَحْرَاء → صَحْرَاوَانِ",
        "Transformed hamza (منقلبة): can stay or change - بِنَاء → بِنَاءَانِ/بِنَاوَانِ",
        "Feminine form: add ة after dropping اء if for feminization"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "صَحْرَاوَانِ وَاسِعَتَانِ", "english": "Two vast deserts" },
        { "arabic": "الدُّعَاءُ سِلَاحُ الْمُؤْمِنِ", "english": "Supplication is the weapon of the believer" },
        { "arabic": "الْبِنَاءُ عَالٍ", "english": "The building is tall" },
        { "arabic": "الْعَدَاءُ مَمْنُوعٌ", "english": "Running is prohibited" }
      ]
    }
